		<div class="qna-section" style="padding-bottom:20px;">
			<div class="question">Question 7:Any extra advice to your juniors for technical skills that they should develop?</div>

			<div class="answer">Answer:  It all depends on the field you are preparing for. If you are preparing for core then go for pcb designing. If you are into full-stack web development then try to learn more about deployment (like secure keys-SSL) as well and don't ignore React and other front-end development stuff. But these are the skills that you will eventually develop. For me the most important skill that one sould develop are soft skills. You should know how to introduce yourself. You will face both success and failure in your life. You should learn to treat them equally. Stay calm and focused. Success might take time but it will come to you if you work for it relentlessly. Improve yourself. Learn something new everyday. Make friends. Value them. Go out with them. Finally, all the best to anyone reading this.</div>
